        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:03PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 303 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Greers Ferry, or 8 miles east of Fairfield Bay, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greers Ferry...                   Ben...
Hanover...                        Prim...
Luber...                          Hill Creek Recreation Area...
Brownsville...                    Woodrow...
Edgemont...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
